descriptionHtml:
TechGig is a dynamic, young and an enthusiastic technology company, offering cutting-edge solutions to its clients using innovative technologies. We help our business partners realise their true talent and business potential using our specialised skill assessment, community engagement and recruitment solutions.
TechGig’s journey started in 2010, when India’s biggest digital media conglomerate – The Times Internet Ltd – conceived a word-class platform that could bring all IT professionals, industry leaders, corporate honchos, influencers, decisions makers on one super-engaged platform.

TechGig’s flight started with baby steps and in just two decades we are proud to host 3.8 million+ developers and 627+ companies on one platform. ---hackathon/contest numbers
With so much happening on our platform, we won the Limca Book of Records and Guinness Book of World Records for our mega-hackathon – Code Gladiators.
Here’s a list of contests and hackathons that keep us busy:

Assess Online (hyperlink https://engage.techgig.com/assessments) - Smart solution for school teachers to assess students on various courses and grades.
Code Learn (hyperlink https://engage.techgig.com/assessments) - Easy to use assessment and learning tools for colleges.

LiveCode (hyperlink https://engage.techgig.com/interview) – Conduct live interviews and coding tests remotely.

Code Judge – Find pre-assessed top tech-talent for your firm.

TechGig’s 3.8 million+ competent developers belong to all walks of life - IT professionals, freshers and students – and are eager to ‘learn’ cutting edge tools, ‘compete’ on new-age technologies, and ‘grow’ collectively by knowledge-sharing. We encourage technologists to exchange ideas, showcase their innovative work and network with the IT community and leaders at our various forums, platforms and webinars.

TechGig hosts three marquee technology events annually, which are revered in the IT industry and developers’ communities alike – Code Gladiators, Geek Goddess and Code Wizards.
Code Gladiators is a Guinness World Record holder for being the largest programming event in 2017.
Geek Goddess is a coding contest exclusively for women in technology and helps in identifying top women developers in India.
Code Wizards is India's biggest inter-college competition designed to identify and encourage aspiring coders so that they succeed in their respective careers.

Here’s where to reach us:

descriptionHtml:
TechGig is a dynamic, young and an enthusiastic technology company, offering cutting-edge solutions to its clients using innovative technologies. We help our business partners realise their true talent and business potential using our specialised skill assessment, community engagement and recruitment solutions.
TechGig’s journey started in 2010, when India’s biggest digital media conglomerate – The Times Internet Ltd – conceived a word-class platform that could bring all IT professionals, industry leaders, corporate honchos, influencers, decisions makers on one super-engaged platform.

TechGig’s flight started with baby steps and in just two decades we are proud to host 3.8 million+ developers and 627+ companies on one platform. ---hackathon/contest numbers
With so much happening on our platform, we won the Limca Book of Records and Guinness Book of World Records for our mega-hackathon – Code Gladiators.
Here’s a list of contests and hackathons that keep us busy:

Assess Online (hyperlink https://engage.techgig.com/assessments) - Smart solution for school teachers to assess students on various courses and grades.
Code Learn (hyperlink https://engage.techgig.com/assessments) - Easy to use assessment and learning tools for colleges.

LiveCode (hyperlink https://engage.techgig.com/interview) – Conduct live interviews and coding tests remotely.

Code Judge – Find pre-assessed top tech-talent for your firm.

TechGig’s 3.8 million+ competent developers belong to all walks of life - IT professionals, freshers and students – and are eager to ‘learn’ cutting edge tools, ‘compete’ on new-age technologies, and ‘grow’ collectively by knowledge-sharing. We encourage technologists to exchange ideas, showcase their innovative work and network with the IT community and leaders at our various forums, platforms and webinars.

TechGig hosts three marquee technology events annually, which are revered in the IT industry and developers’ communities alike – Code Gladiators, Geek Goddess and Code Wizards.
Code Gladiators is a Guinness World Record holder for being the largest programming event in 2017.
Geek Goddess is a coding contest exclusively for women in technology and helps in identifying top women developers in India.
Code Wizards is India's biggest inter-college competition designed to identify and encourage aspiring coders so that they succeed in their respective careers.

Here’s where to reach us:

Social media –

LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/techgigdotcom/
